Thank you, thank for for teaching me how to love myself. Twice. I came back from hatred, twice. Thank you for saving my life.
this is my 3rd 30 day challenge! thank you so much Adrienne. <3 first time I was able to go through the entire self guided last day, yoga with Adrienne has changed my relationship with myself 💘

Been following and doing the practices for a long time. Every month start a new 30 day practice. Very good for the start of the morning and rest of the day.

2 minor comments. 1) would be good to have shorter sessions like 20min. I know some of the newer ones have them.

And 2) the end message is “may all beings be free and happy” which I 100% agree with. But then Adrienne says she can’t give up eggs and fish. Don’t think those eggs and fish are free and/or happy being served as a meal?

Not trolling…as mentioned I follow the yoga practices and will continue to do so.

But the message vs the practice of not following the message seems to be a disconnect.

Peace.
Thank you Adriene. I feel so grateful. God bless you.

Im just done

You taught me well, Ariene. That’s 60 days of yoga done. Which 30 day programme to choose next?

Finished this journey that I started this past April. I had originally aligned the time to be 30 days until I was home from college but a run gone bad led me to fracture my tibial plateau and to have knee surgery. I remember crying the night after the injury because yoga gives me so much joy and I wouldn't be able to do it for a long time. Well, here I am. Finishing what I started. My mantra for today was "I am awesome". Thanks, Adriene! You've felt like a pal for a long time <3
Eternally grateful for you. Namaste
60 días of yoga. Today was so hard but I made it. ❤️

Thank you, Adrienne! You are a wonderful teacher. And the end of last the yoga camp video was perfekt. I loved hearing the full closing song, seeing the waterfall up close and your personal message. It made me feel so emotional as it was a beautiful journey! I'm looking forward to start the next 30days of yoga with you tomorrow 😁
Silent 🤫 is magic in it 🎉y

wow that was my third 30days and I can believe how good my body feels and how much I enjoy the poses thankyou :-)

I can't put into words how you and your classes has transformed my life but imma try. Before the start of this year  I began my first 30 day yoga journey, we're almost in July and every aspect of my health has changed and blossomed! My mental health is the best it's ever been, my spiritual, emotional and physical health has followed suit and even the darker days aren't as dark as they used to be, I feel so emotional writing this, the biggest comment I've ever left on YouTube 😂 but seriously from the core of my heart and soul thankyou I didn't ever imagine I'd feel as good as I do so soon! I'm infinitely greatful!!! We love you so much 💫

Thank you! Thank you! Thank you! I truly love you and your channel. I am so grateful that you are doing what you are doing.

I have been able to do things with my body that I never thought possible. I have challenged myself and have been determined to follow through with daily yoga. I am so pleased with the results. 

I must say that this flow from day 30 is hands down my favorite flow of any yoga flow I've ever done. It was perfect.I will be coming back to this video again and again in the future I already know. 

Thank you Adriene for following your gut and your intuition and creating such a wonderful platform for yogis of all stages and walks of life to come to and learn yoga. I just completed 30 days yoga camp. I can't believe I actually did it. Thank you so much Adriene for this beautiful experience. This marks my 60th day of intentional daily yoga. Next stop... revolution 💪. Thank you for everything. I'm really glad I found you. Yoga with Adriene has changed my yoga practice forever.

Dear Adriene, 30 days ago I was knew to yoga, I did a couple of your videos years ago but I took this yoga camp seriously and it was effortless to go to the mat. You made me discover an inner side of me that was asleep. I'm full of gratitude for having you guiding me. Thank you. I'll continue with another of your 30 days.

Thank you Adrienne. I can't possibly express how your videos have helped me fight depression at my lowest, and how it is now the first thing I look forward to every single day. It is what makes me want to get out of bed and it makes me want to start the day a happy person. I love your voice. I love smiling and laughing with you at your jokes. I love feeling the things you instil in us through your voice and practice. When I did 30 days of yoga and also the majority of yoga camp, it was all about this feeling for me, the feeling of coming home to myself but now I can also see my body loving it and looking forward to it. I feel so much stronger physically and mentally and I can't thank you enough for being an indispensable part of my journey and now my life. THANK YOU.
What an incredible 30 days!  Although I am quite late to the party :-), I am so glad to have found this.  Thank you and looking forward to another one!

These 30 days, the experience you helped us create and the community of yogis are all so special and I feel so blessed to be here💖

I know you made this many years ago, but I started doing all the 30-day challenges from the beginning through the pandemic. Life got in the way and I stopped doing it so consistently for a while, but yesterday I had a really hard conflict for me to deal with that still stayed with me this morning. I did this yoga sequence to help calm myself, and throughout it, I started saying "I love myself" and "I love you" and realized I meant it. Towards the end, I started listing the people in my life who love me unconditionally and, though nothing is "solved" I feel less alone. Thank you for all that you do :)

Finished Camp yesterday and I swear I'm still flying high. 🙏 This was my 5th 30 day journey with Adriene and I think it may be a top favorite now. I was so moved by it and it changed my heart. Today is day 118 of yoga every day with Adriene and I can't imagine my life without her and my expanded home practice. ❤ Thank you from the bottom of my soul, Adriene ❤

As soon as Adriene said 'freestyle' I was like 'eugh no way, I like being guided and told what to do'. But then I saw her start by just lying down and I figured I could give that a go. I found myself really listening to my body and doing exactly what it wanted! I put together a pretty good little practice I think.... and only the last 10 minutes or so were spent lying down in shavasna!! Proud to have got to the end of the 30 day journey, even if it has taken me about 6 weeks due to a few breaks here and there!

I have done a few of Adriene's 30-day series, but this is the first time I've done the whole freestyle practice with my eyes closed. It really helped me connect with my chosen mantra ("I am present") as I was more focused on the movement, but definitely made the balancing poses more challenging! :D This was a really great yoga series, thanks Adriene!

i was a little intimidated by this video. last 30 days, i pretty much just followed along with adriene for the whole video. i started that way this time but found myself branching out and finding my own practice for the very first time. about halfway through, the perfect mantra hit me: i explore. thank you, adriene. <3
What's the song at 19:16??

Today was day 30 of my sixth 30-day yoga journey with Adriene. It's been a few years of going on these journeys interspersed with Adriene's other videos in between. Today felt so freeing (and definitely emotional as all day 30s seem to be!) because for the first time on day 30, I barely looked at the video. I mostly free-styled and found what felt good. At one point when I was attempting crow hoping to get it today, I glanced over and Adriene was doing it too! That was cool. I kinda held it for a second but realized I'll have to keep working on it. Thank you SO much Adriene and the community for being such an important part of my life. Namaste. ❤️

Like some others here, I am very, very rarely one for commenting on YouTube. But I really wanted to say thank you, Adriene, for putting so much thought, effort and energy into these videos, and for making them so widely available. You've had such a positive impact on my flexibility (so close to heels on the ground with downward dog now!), ability to move my body, thoughts, emotions—everything.

This last practice hit home for me in a pretty profound way. My mantra for today was, "I am happy". I truly hope that you continue to spread the message about yoga to people (like me) who never thought they would, or could, do it. I hope that I continue to grow the practice that I have cultivated over the last 6 months through your videos. And most of all, I hope that you, too, are happy.

Find what feels good!

⏳ And just like that, another 30 Day Challenge comes to an end. 🙏  It's so crazy to look back and see how Day 1 became Day 14...30.. now 60. I've learned a lot, and am excited to learn so much more. 

Yoga has become a friend that checks in daily with me to see how everything is going. Because of this, I'm more conscious of the decisions I make. If the day leaves me drained, I get to examine it; but if I feel energized, I can keep and nurture those things. The email this week with John O'Donahue's poem was really amazing, especially this line:

"The darkened days that stopped
The confidence of the dawn."

I feel like I've picked up where I left off before life became really hectic (in the darkened days) this year, and with the confidence and energy from you and Yoga, I will be able to challenge the new (and some old) difficulties ahead. 

There's much I would like to do for people who are trying to better their lives, but as you've pointed out: we have to nurture ourselves so that we can nurture others.

I'm really looking forward for the new "Home" Yoga journey, and for "Yoga For Transitions" practice tonight for NYE.

Today was my second 30th day. Unlike the first time, when I finished the 30 days of yoga practice, this time I felt comfortable with improvising. As soon as the music started I closed my eyes and jumped deep into it. It was me telling me what to do, it was me finding what felt good. At first the mantra was “I’m in control”, but the deeper I dove the fuzzier the mantra became. I opened my eyes, and could not believe what I saw: You and I both solidly in our warrior position... I felt connection, like I never felt before. I found confirmation, “I Am Free” !!!
I said it loud, I felt it strong. And then the music brought me to the safest harbor of practice end. We bowed a sincere and wordless Namaste...
Tear drops...
And it felt soooooo good

I didn't expect today to make me so emotional. I've been practicing with you for three years now. I did True and Dedicate as it came out, and after Dedicate I wanted to work my way through all of the 30 Day Journeys and back, with some days to catch up on your newly posted videos. Right after Revolution, I dislocated my dominant shoulder acting in a movie, pitching an apple, a cute idea that wasn't even in the script and i never had been injured before. This injury robbed me of my yoga, my music playing ability and kept me from working on my new home this summer. I've been in Physical Therapy for several months, and had a sling on for three. I was so scared I reached out to the Kula community for support before my FB friends or Insta followers. Someone in the community told me ' I have the opportunity to learn the REAL healing power of yoga' initially, that pissed me off SO bad, but probably because I knew it was true, and it was. I still practiced finding what felt good with the sling on, but before my arm popped out I was JUST beginning to hit the arm balances, and for the first time in my life feeling strong. Today I FINALLY finished Yoga Camp. I started 30 days ago, and I feel strong again. I realize I can heal to do what I've done before and to go beyond, the community was right. I am learning the healing power of yoga. I leave tomorrow to go on a big trip to finishing acting in the movie i hurt myself on, then act in two feature films and fly in a plane for the first time in my life. I feel strong and supported in myself, and not nearly as afraid as I was 30 days ago. As a fellow actor & artist, I just can't thank you enough for what you've shared with me and everyone else. This practice keeps me calm cool and collected as I try to create relentlessly and hone my intensity. Thank you Adriene. I'll be in Austin working on a film Oct-Nov and will be watching your emails to see if any local classes come up! Every time you're on the East Coast I end up being somewhere else! I hope our paths cross someday but until then I will be sending you positive vibes in your journey and finding what feels good in mine! Much love!!! <3

On Jan 5 I made a promise to myself that I would do both Yoga Camp and 30 Days of Yoga with Adriene every day. This practice has been eye-opening. I've finally found what feels good and that's yoga, with Adriene. Now onto Revolution.

Day 30 Check.

So, I guess I'll have to conclude it right here. I'm going to have to be brutally honest and say it: I'm kind of disappointed. I was hoping that by doing this that I would change, that I would be more flexible or feel a bit more better, or something. I still stumble on some of my poses, I still have to lift my heels at downward dogs, I can't keep my balance when my balance was required, I don't know. Maybe Yoga is not for me. And it's really disappointing and painful to say that. I feel really terrible saying this, I really do. And I've been waiting for a reply to the questions that I've been asking and no one has replied to them, which made me feel kind of left out and disconnected when this is supposed to be a community about connection. 

I seriously don't know. Maybe I missed something? I did all 30 days and if I missed one day, I would do two sessions the next day. Maybe I have to do more Yoga? I... I don't know. I'm just loss.

All this aside though, I appreciate the passion, work, effort, and time put into these videos by your Adriene. I just only wish that I didn't feel so hollow at the end of it all. I don't know whether I should continue or find something else... I don't know..

I just want to say that I welcome everyone's retort on this matter. Not only that, I implore someone to make a retort on this. I'm not trying to be negative, in fact, I started this because I wanted to stop being negative and change myself. Again, it's just so painful to admit no change to this. I wanted guarantee that there would be something different about it. Sigh. I don't know. Maybe I'm thinking way into this or maybe I'm still negative and really haven't change. That would make me sad. 

Anyways, regardless of this, I'd like to thank Adirene for really doing her best at making these videos. I only wish that my forms were just as beautiful as yours. Maybe I need some time off and think about it. I only wish that I didn't feel this way at the end of it all. Thank you Adirene, you are the best.

I cried at the end of this video and I feel so much gratitude and love towards Adriene for Yoga Camp and 30 days of Yoga. Over the past year i've struggled hugely with anxiety and generally being unhappy and a bit of a recluse. But 30 days of Yoga showed me I can commit to something for a full 30 days, and Yoga Camp showed me how to speak positively to myself, and how to love myself. Because it's all well and good telling someone they should love themselves, but providing them with the tools to do so often gets missed out. So thank you Adriene for helping me grow and cultivate a practice and lifestyle which serves me. Finished! But really just beginning to feel much of the change I've wanted for such a long time. Today's free form was tough to "not follow." But I'm going to loosen up and try it again tomorrow. 

I am So. Much. Stronger. While my crow pose is still just a single deep-breath glimpse of strength and balance, I'm proud to say I haven't collapsed on my wrists and face in weeks. Every day, I try it again: navel to spine, gaze forward, lengthening the shoulders away from the ears. I hear this guidance and follow it beyond practice, throughout my day: walking the halls of the school where I teach; schlepping my kids in the minivan from piano to soccer to baseball; folding laundry; washing dishes; planning the week with my husband; sitting over cocktails with friends. My practice is more than just the minutes of the video, it's all the minutes of my day -- treasures, every one of them. You have reminded me of that. A zillion blessings upon you, Adriene. Love!

Hello Adriene,

my name is Tine and I'm 23 years old. I live in Germany and study primary school teaching.

I just wanted to tell you how much your videos mean to me. I started last year with the first 30 Days of Yoga Challenge and loved it from the beginning! It's so good that you always give options and also that you include this positive body image, which for me is equally to or even more than the poses what yoga is all about.
The funny thing is, last year I was a little lost with day 30. Like some other people commented, it's a bit scary that there is no voice to guide you. This year was different. I looked forward to it! I noticed that I sometimes forgot about the breathing, but hey, I still have so much to learn..

Since I'm going to be a teacher one day, I thought about getting an education in teaching yoga to kids. Because for me, before I practiced yoga, I had this really undefined image of my body. Nowadays I know that there are things which I'm not completely satisfied with, but I know what I have and with yoga I learn to love myself everyday a bit more (so cheesy :D).

So what my point is: I think it could be really good for children to get to know their bodies and what they're capable of and especially with puberty coming up. There's so much confusion about themselves and their bodies are changing and I think Yoga could help to keep them stable somehow. Maybe. Hopefully!
(If there's someone out there who already does that, please share your experiences!)

Sorry for the long read, but I really wanted you to know how I grateful I am and how much you influenced my life in a positive way.

Liebe Grüße,
Tine

Dear dear dear Adriene, I am soooooo very grateful for you coming into my world, you are a divine yogi and I am so very blessed to have learned so much from you these last 30 days. My mantra today was 'I am proud'...of the journey I have taken, to be able to connect my mind and body and to be here on my mat today on day 30 (holly cow never thought I could do it!!!!!)! I loved today's mantra, because you taught me the most important lesson! I hadn't expected to guide todays practice by myself and at some point I wasn't feeling it (no inspiration for what to do next) so I thought I'd follow you but that was hard for me without your voice while trying to breathe and feel my body ALL AT THE SAME TIME whaaaaaa... and so, little ol'  me felt frustrated and abandoned there for a moment:), until I realized: 

it's okay to get lost, to get frustrated, to not love the pose - and still feel worthy about my practice! So that's my biggest achievement after 30 days: just allow myself to be me, and feel everything I feel without passing judgment and admitting to myself I am here to learn and to experience, including the things that don't go perfectly. And I am not aiming to be perfect, thank god. And then I cried (yes me too), all happy tears... So today was a wonderful ending to my beautiful journey with you. A million thanks!!!!!!!!!!!

Dear Adriene,
I finished the yoga comp on Tuesday. I wanted the time to thank you for the experience but at the time I found it difficult to find the words. I want to thank you from the bottom of my heart. It took me 39 days to complete the camp but I accept that. In 39 days I have done more yoga than in the 23 years prior to it! I have come to enjoy my home practice and I truly found what feels good, especially on day 30. At first I followed your lead I realized that a was strong enough to trust myself to follow my own lead and I went with the flow. I enjoyed and celebrated that last day and I find myself falling in love with yoga. 
Perhaps in the future I will find a yoga studio in my area so someone trained can help me become better but for now I enjoy the at home practice immensely. I deserve to take that time for myself. Thank you for all the lessons I have learned during camp and for all the lessons you will teach me in the future.

Sincerely Hanna Swenne from the Netherlands

The first reason is because I work at a hospital; during terrible winter weather when the entire midwest is closed down for a day or two, I report to work as "essential personnel." My other reason also comes from working at a hospital. Sometimes I see emotionally awful things. Sometimes I have to put on a poker face in the midst of little hope. I have to block some things out and just keep rolling during a busy day... then sometimes I get home and it hits me what I saw. Today I had a few of those "sometimes." But what I do is essential. Because I am essential.

Thank you for the opportunity to remind myself of that today.
